(576, 1, '2015-01-30 11:10:03', '2015-01-30 10:10:03', 'We <strong>care</strong> because we <strong>share</strong>\r\n<h2>Passion…</h2>\r\nYou don’t stay in the same industry for more than 15 years by coincidence. Ongoing learning allows us to keep developing our expertise, mastering for example the latest technology related to the translation industry. Most importantly, our relationships with the different stakeholders (clients, translators, etc.) are growing far beyond our expectations. It also feels great when we know clients are satisfied and they let us know. A passion for what you do is really what keeps you alive and kicking – and that’s the defining difference of Sparkling <strong>Lengua</strong>!\r\n<h2>We’ll find a way to make it work!</h2>\r\nWe are proactive optimists and we believe "<strong>where there’s a will, there’s a way</strong>". For that reason, we don’t automatically jump to the conclusion that a deadline is impossible. Our first goal is to make your deadline possible and we will make relentless efforts to reach the most optimal result/solution for you. We have long&#8239;standing relationships with partners who continue to surprise us about how fast they can deliver high&#8239;quality results on last-minute projects. We are proud to say that we have often helped our clients by turning "mission impossible" jobs into <strong>success stories</strong>.\r\n<h2>Beyond our projects are dedicated people</h2>\r\nThe biggest part of our daily work is interaction with people, so there is a strong emphasis on <strong>communication and psychology</strong>. Our experience has taught us that to truly succeed in the localization business, you also need patience and humor, along with a real desire to help and understand people. Sharing this commitment, our partners are flexible; they like their work and are proud of it.\r\n<h2>Quasi-colleagues…</h2>\r\nWe take a respectful, proactive approach to "partner" with our clients. A good translation and localization company is <strong>more than just a vendor</strong>, and here’s why: A top quality translation, transcreation or localization project begins with thorough preparation, wich involves  input from all players at the table (and their expectations), asking the right questions and sharing information. This foundation is built on trust and supported by excellent skills and tools, reliable response times and attentive service. No matter how complex a project is or how quickly it has to be done, it can be completed happily if translation partners agree "we are in this together and we all have the same goal". This approach has earned Sparkling <strong>Lengua</strong> much repeat business and <strong>sets us apart from others</strong>!', 'Our philosophy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-30 11:10:03', '2015-01-30 10:10:03', '', 11, 'http://www.sparklinglengua.com/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
